1 Histogram of Old Faithful waiting times

As you know, every time you open a new shiny app RStudio creates the default Old Faithful app. In particular, this app displays a histogram to visualize the distribution of waiting times, and lets you choose the number of bins with a slider widget (see screenshot below).


2 Histogram with "ggplot2" functions

Instead of using the hist() function to make the histogram, we are going to use functions from the tidyverse package "ggplot2", which means we need to load "tidyverse"

library(tidyverse)

To make a histogram of waiting times we need to use ggplot() and the layer geom_histogram(). The good news is that geom_histogram() comes with the bins argument which allows you to specify the number of bins to be used in the displayed distribution.

2.1 Example

Hereâs some ggplot code to make a histogram of waiting times:

ggplot(data = faithful, aes(x = waiting)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 10, color = "white") +
  labs(x = "waiting times (mins)")

Important

How would you modify the preceding command in order to:

  • fill the bars of the histogram with your favorite color

  • include a meaningful title for the histogram

  • customize the appearance of the graphic with one of the custom themes; e.g.Â  theme_minimal()
